### 1. Create a new User (POST)
# Expected: 201 Created
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/user
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "address": "123 Main St, Paris",
  "phoneNumber": "0123456789",
  "birthDate": "1990-01-01"
}

### 2. Get all Users (GET)
# Expected: 200 OK (List of users)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/user

### 3. Get User by ID (GET)
# Replace '1' with the actual ID if different
# Expected: 200 OK
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/user/1

### 4. Update User (PUT)
# We update ONLY the phone and address.
# Expected: 200 OK
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/user/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "0987654321",
  "address": "456 New Avenue, Lyon"
}

### 5. Verify Update (GET)
# Check if phone changed BUT firstName remains "John".
# If firstName is null here, you have the "Null Trap" bug.
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/user/1

### 6. Test Error: Duplicate Email (POST)
# Try creating another user with the SAME email.
# Expected: 400 Bad Request
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/user
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "address": "Different Address",
  "phoneNumber": "1112223333",
  "birthDate": "1995-05-05"
}

### 7. Delete User (DELETE)
# Expected: 204 No Content
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/v1/user/1

### 8. Verify Deletion (GET)
# Expected: 404 Not Found
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/user/1